intp (0.2.0~placeholder-1) noble; urgency=low

  * Add intp_probe_ebpf() public API + `intp --probe` CLI command:
    asks libbpf whether the kernel accepts a kprobe-type BPF program
    and reports OK / kernel-too-old / not-permitted / unsupported.
    Loads no persistent program; safe for unprivileged callers.
    Pulls libbpf into libintp1's runtime Depends (auto-resolved by
    dh_shlibdeps).
  * Add intp_serve_prometheus() public API + `intp --serve` CLI mode:
    libmicrohttpd-based HTTP server that exposes /metrics in the
    canonical Prometheus text format. The seven core metrics are
    exposed with placeholder zero values and status="placeholder";
    intp_metrics_implemented advertises 0 to make the half-built
    state legible to scrapers. Stage 2 wires the live sampling loop
    into the same endpoint with no API change. Pulls libmicrohttpd
    into libintp1's runtime Depends.
  * Bump upstream version to 0.2.0 to reflect the API additions
    (backward-compatible; SONAME stays libintp.so.0).
  * No metric collection logic added — variant selection between v2
    (pure-C) and v3 (eBPF/CO-RE) remains a Stage 1 decision in
    `intp-comparison`.

 -- André Sacilotto Santos <sacilotto.andre@gmail.com>  Sat, 09 May 2026 17:00:00 +0000

intp (0.1.0~placeholder2-1) noble; urgency=low

  * Re-upload after orig tarball regeneration. The previous
    0.1.0~placeholder-1 orig tarball was created with `git archive`
    run from a subdirectory, which (via cwd-relative pathspec
    matching) captured only packaging/debian/* instead of the full
    upstream tree, so Launchpad's meson configure step found no
    meson.build at the source root.
  * No upstream code changes; this is a pure re-roll of the source
    tarball.

 -- André Sacilotto Santos <sacilotto.andre@gmail.com>  Sat, 09 May 2026 13:30:00 +0000

